 :blast: 1. v.,n. Synonym for {BLT}, used esp. for large data sends over a
network or comm line. Opposite of {snarf}. Usage: uncommon. The variant
`blat' has been reported. 2. vt. [HP/Apollo] Synonymous with {nuke} (sense
3). Sometimes the message Unable to kill all processes. Blast them (y/n)?
would appear in the command window upon logout.